Wow! #teamseas Cleanup
#ourocean coordinated by ICC team Lagos, Nigeria, MCCSN and NIOMR at Marwa beach, Victoria Island, Lagos, Nigeria on the 22nd January can only be described as Amazing. Nearly 200 volunteers from mainly coastal communities removed 136 bags (1622.64kg) of trash that would have otherwise gone into the seas 
A new movement to tackle the scourge of Ocean trash and plastics has been launched with the coastal dwellers taking a giant leap.
Cleaner and Healthier Seas is our aim for Lagos State and Nigeria with our team taking out one pound of trash at a time from our beaches. This is the beginning of teamwork starting with the Marwa coastal communities we intend to partner with individuals, industry, NGOs, community, schools, government and the public to make our coast and beaches plastic free. 
